This article is a press release from the White House Office of the Press Secretary, dated October 3, 2014. It announces an executive order signed by President Barack Obama titled "Conversion Authority for Criminal Investigators (Special Agents) of the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms, and Explosives." 

The executive order grants the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms, and Explosives (ATF) the authority to convert certain positions in the Federal civil service without going through the competitive examination process. Specifically, Criminal Investigators of the ATF who have been appointed under Schedule B and have completed 3 years of satisfactory service may be converted non-competitively to career appointments if they meet the qualifications and requirements set by the Director of the Office of Personnel Management.

The order directs the Director of the Office of Personnel Management to establish regulations necessary for implementing this order. It also includes general provisions stating that the order does not affect the authority of executive departments or the functions of the Director of the Office of Management and Budget, and that it does not create any rights or benefits enforceable against the United States or any other party.